    <item>
      <title>Using VMware.Sdk.Vcf.SddcManager: Commands for SDDC Manager in PowerCLI</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-sddcm-cmdlets/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 17 Jul 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/post/vcf-90/vcf-90-powercli-sddcm-cmdlets/</guid>
      <description>
        
          
            &lt;p&gt;VCF PowerCLI 9.0 now includes a module called &lt;code&gt;VMware.Sdk.Vcf.SddcManager&lt;/code&gt;, this modules contains auto-generated cmdlets to support SDDC Manager Public APIs. Use can use this post as a quick reference guide.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;connecting-to-a-sddc-manager-instance-with-local-credentials&#34;&gt;Connecting to a SDDC Manager Instance with Local Credentials&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start a PowerShell session.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Connect to a SDDC Manager instance using local credentials by running the following command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;Connect-VcfSddcManagerServer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-Server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;sfo-vcf01&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;sfo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;rainpole&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;io&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-User&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;administrator&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;@vsphere&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;local&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-Password&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;VMw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;@re1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;VMw&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nv&#34;&gt;@re1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Once connected the following information is stored in &lt;code&gt;$defaultSddcManagerConnections&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ServiceUri     : https://sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;SessionSecret  : &amp;lt;sessionSecret&amp;gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;User           : administrator@vsphere.local
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;IsConnected    : True
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Id             : /VcfSddcManagerServer&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;administrator@vsphere.local@sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 6&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Name           : sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Uid            : /VcfSddcManagerServer&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;administrator@vsphere.local@sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 8&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ProductVersion : 9.0.0.0.24703748
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt; 9&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ServerUri      : https://sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;10&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;UUID           : /VcfSddcManagerServer&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;administrator@vsphere.local@sfo-vcf01.sfo.rainpole.io:443/
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;11&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;Port           : &lt;span class=&#34;m&#34;&gt;443&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ol start=&#34;4&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disconnect from a SDDC Manager instance by running the following command:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-powershell&#34; data-lang=&#34;powershell&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;ln&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;Disconnect-VcfSddcManagerServer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;-Server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;sfo-vcf01&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;sfo&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;rainpole&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;py&#34;&gt;io&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;display-all-sddc-manager-get-command-details&#34;&gt;Display All SDDC Manager GET Command Details&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Start a PowerShell session.&lt;/p&gt;
          
          
        
      </description>
